&lt;p&gt;An exciting new role for a Practice Development Nurse in Cardiology has become available at the Luton and Dunstable Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a committed, engaging and proactive nurse to take on this new position in Cardiology supporting the development of our Cardiology nursing team. This is a development post into a band 7 position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Whilst Cardiology is going through a transitional period of its complex service due to the current pandemic situation this supportive role, more than ever, will be paramount developing our team of nurses in practice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to support the development of nurses working within cardiology to ensure they are equipped to care for the spectrum of cardiology patients, support the on-going Trust learning programmes and identify educational opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joao Barros - Matron for Specialist Medicine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;joao.de-barros@ldh.nhs.uk  Bleep 044&lt;/p&gt;
